:QUOTE
Every town deserves a radio station that sounds like itself.

:INFO
Online Community Radio Station
Launch an internet radio station for your neighborhood, town, or interest community using free and open-source tools. AzuraCast makes it possible to run a professional stream from a single server.

:COUNTER.half
$10/Month
Minimum hosting cost for a 24/7 stream
|
:COUNTER.half
10 DJs
Good starting size for a programming roster

:PATH
Choose Your Software
AzuraCast is the recommended self-hosted option. Install on a $6 DigitalOcean droplet. It includes AutoDJ, a web interface for DJs, scheduling, and listener analytics built in.

:PATH
Build Your Programming
Mix live shows with AutoDJ filler. Recruit local musicians, storytellers, and community voices. Create a weekly schedule and hold to it so listeners can form habits.

:PATH
Build the Community
Stream to your website and add a Mixcloud or SoundCloud archive. Post show recordings to a community Discord. Create a local artist spotlight series to draw in musicians.

:CHECKLIST
Launch Checklist
[ ] Register a domain for the station
[ ] Spin up a VPS and install AzuraCast
[ ] Upload 8 hours of filler music cleared for broadcast
[ ] Recruit 3 show hosts for the first schedule
[ ] Set up a station Discord for DJs and listeners
[ ] Embed the stream player on your website
[ ] Announce on local Facebook and Nextdoor

:NOTE
Check your country's music licensing rules before going live. In the US you may need a SoundExchange license for streaming. Many stations start with podsafe and Creative Commons music to avoid fees early on.
